LAYOUT (TEXT="Generic Menu Test")
GRID
{
Style   [d01                                             ]
Image   [d02                                             ]
Comment [d03                                             ]
<T                                                       >
 [c01       |c02         |c03       |c04                ]
 [c01       |c02         |c03       |c04                ]
 [c01       |c02         |c03       |c04                ]
 [c01       |c02         |c03       |c04                ]
 [c01       |c02         |c03       |c04                ]
<                                                        >
[bg01                                                    ]

 In this example, you can build up a menu generically i.e. maybe from a 
 database or set of configuration files. Type into the array some additional
 menu entries and click the button. The only restriction is the maximum
 number of entries, in this instance 20. I haven't got them here but you
 could add other methods to change the accelerator attribtue.
}
END
END

ATTRIBUTES

COMBOBOX d01 = formonly.style, ITEMS=(("dialog","Dialog"),("popup","Popup")), COMMENT="Enter the menu style";
EDIT d02 = formonly.image, SCROLL, COMMENT="Enter the menu image";
EDIT d03 = formonly.comment, SCROLL, COMMENT="Enter the menu comment";

EDIT c01 = formonly.name, SCROLL, COMMENT = "Enter the menu item action name", TITLE="Name";
EDIT c02 = formonly.text, SCROLL, COMMENT="Enter the menu item text", TITLE="Text";
EDIT c03 = formonly.item_image, SCROLL, COMMENT="Enter the menu item image", TITLE="Image";
EDIT c04 = formonly.item_comment, SCROLL, COMMENT="Enter the menu item comment", TITLE="Comment";
BUTTON bg01: menu, TEXT="Show Menu", COMMENT="Show menu";

INSTRUCTIONS
SCREEN RECORD scr(name,text,item_image,item_comment);
